{"word":"αἱμάσσω","slug":"αἱμάσσω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>αἱμάσσω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:αἷμα'><el>αἷμα</el></a>\n<p/><i>to make bloody stain with blood</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>:—hence <i>to smite so as to make bloody</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; so in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to welter in blood, be slain</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/>"}]}